Mango Pie
via navixeon

Crust:
2 1/2 cups all purpose flour
1/2 teaspoon salt
5 Tablespoons chilled butter, cut in small pieces
3 Tablespoons vegetable shortening, chilled
10 Tablespoons ice water
cooking spray (??? i never use this but whatever)

Filling:
2/3 cup packed brown sugar
3 Tablespoons cornstarch (once i messed up and made the crust with cornstarch. that was funny. i thought it was flour. i was very drunk with my mother)
4 1/2 cups mango wedges (about 4 medium mangos)
1 Tablespoon chilled butter, cut into pieces (i never add this extra butter)

Topping:
1 1/2 teaspoons fat free milk (or soy)
1 Tablespoon granulated sugar
as much crystallized ginger as you want to chop to sprinkle on top


1. Combine flour and salt-stir with whisk. Cut in 5 Tablespoons butter and shortening (use pastry blender or 2 knives) until the mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add water, stirring just until moist. Divide dough into two equal portions. Press each portion into a 4 inch circle. Wrap and chill 30 minutes.

2. preheat oven to 425 F

3. Unwrap dough; Roll 1 portion out on floured surface. Roll dough into a 12 inch circle. Fit into a 10 inch deep dish pie plate (coated with cooking spray)

4. Filling time! Combine brown sugar and cornstarch in a bowl. Add cut mango slices and toss to coat. Add mango mixture to pie plate and sprinkle with butter

5. Unwrap 2 portion dough. Roll into 12 inch circle and fit over pie. Press edges together, cut slits.

6. Topping: brush pie with milk. Combine ginger and sugar and sprinkle on top of pie. Place pie plate on foil lined baking sheet

7. Bake at 425 for 20 minutes. Reduce oven temp to 375 and bake additional 30 minutes or until pie is golden brown.

Calories per slice: 274 (30% from fat), Fat: 9.1g, Protein: 3.1g, Fiber: 1.8g, Chol: 15mg, Iron: 1.6mg, Sodium: 146mg, Calcium: 25mg
